WEBVTT

00:00:00.034 --> 00:00:04.279
Well, we are in a collection of messages that we have called The River Wild.

00:00:04.299 --> 00:00:09.245
We're taking time this spring to look at some of the amazing realities, river stories in scripture.

00:00:09.286 --> 00:00:13.451
And today, if you have a Bible, we're going to be in Ezekiel, chapter 47.

00:00:13.731 --> 00:00:19.899
Of course, you do get 10 brownie points if you can make your way successfully to the book of Ezekiel in your Bible.

00:00:20.660 --> 00:00:29.010
And I want to give you a message that I'm calling with deepest appreciation to the man in black, five feet high and rising.

00:00:29.794 --> 00:00:37.445
Five feet high and rising, this is what Ezekiel had to say in the 47th chapter of his prophetic book.

00:00:39.008 --> 00:00:44.516
He said, then he brought me back to the door of the temple.

00:00:45.678 --> 00:00:53.730
There was water flowing from under the threshold of the temple toward the east, for the front of the temple faced east.

00:00:54.731 --> 00:00:59.378
The water was flowing from under the right side of the temple south of the altar.

00:01:00.386 --> 00:01:03.229
He brought me out by way of the north gate.

00:01:04.270 --> 00:01:08.354
And he led me around on the outside to the outer gateway that faces east.

00:01:09.255 --> 00:01:12.398
And there was water running out on the right side.

00:01:13.459 --> 00:01:18.324
And when the man went out to the east with the line in his hand, he measured 1,000 cubits.

00:01:19.304 --> 00:01:20.686
And he brought me through the waters.

00:01:21.286 --> 00:01:22.868
The water came up to my ankles.

00:01:23.789 --> 00:01:26.772
Again, he measured 1,000 and brought me through the waters.

00:01:27.292 --> 00:01:29.074
The water came up to my knees.

00:01:29.570 --> 00:01:35.238
Again, he measured 1,000 and brought me through the water, and it came up to my waist.

00:01:36.180 --> 00:01:49.740
Again, he measured 1,000, and it was a river that I could not cross, for the water was too deep, water in which one must swim, a river that could not be crossed.

00:01:50.681 --> 00:01:53.145
He said to me, son of man, have you seen this?

00:01:54.346 --> 00:01:57.571
And he brought me and returned me to the bank of the river.

00:01:58.573 --> 00:01:59.474
When I returned,

00:02:00.162 --> 00:02:05.931
There along the bank of the river, there were very many trees on one side and on the other.

00:02:07.072 --> 00:02:13.562
Then he said to me, this water flows toward the eastern region, goes down into the valley and enters the sea.

00:02:14.523 --> 00:02:17.608
When it reaches the sea, its waters are healed.

00:02:18.990 --> 00:02:26.962
And it shall be that every living thing that moves, whether wherever the rivers go will live,

00:02:27.202 --> 00:02:30.225
One translation says, wherever the rivers go, it turns fresh.

00:02:32.187 --> 00:02:42.897
There will be a very great multitude of fish, because these waters go there, for they will be healed, and everything will live, or everything will be fresh wherever this river goes.

00:02:44.118 --> 00:02:48.763
It shall be that fishermen will stand by it from Ngedi all the way to En Iglaim.

00:02:49.403 --> 00:02:51.886
They will be places for spreading their nets.

00:02:52.807 --> 00:02:56.370
Their fish will be of the same kinds as the fish of the Great Sea.

00:02:56.738 --> 00:02:57.840
exceedingly many.

00:02:58.761 --> 00:03:01.825
But its swamps and marshes will not be healed.

00:03:01.886 --> 00:03:03.568
They will be given over to salt.

00:03:05.050 --> 00:03:12.641
Along the bank of the river, on this side and that, will grow all kinds of trees used for food.

00:03:13.282 --> 00:03:17.188
Their leaves will not wither and their fruit will not fail.

00:03:17.248 --> 00:03:24.018
They will bear fruit every month because their water flows from the sanctuary.

00:03:24.706 --> 00:03:30.533
Their fruit will be for food and their leaves for medicine.

00:03:32.676 --> 00:03:35.660
And God, we thank you for this.

00:03:38.263 --> 00:03:42.869
We feel a little bit like we're standing in front of a magnificent painting in an art gallery.

00:03:42.889 --> 00:03:52.722
We don't quite know whether the goal is for us to understand the use of light, to understand what the artist was doing here, or simply just to bask in it for a second.

00:03:55.234 --> 00:04:11.272
But as we, for these moments, consider what you're trying to say to us through this powerful chapter, I pray that our minds would stop from just trying to worry over these things and trying to puzzle over these things.

00:04:11.352 --> 00:04:23.346
And we would just simply sit back and take it in and have ears to hear what you're saying to us because we realize that there are things you want to do in our lives.

00:04:25.314 --> 00:04:31.002
that are unlocked by seeing a glimpse of the way this river flowed from this vision.

00:04:32.964 --> 00:04:35.348
We pray this in Jesus' name.

00:04:36.870 --> 00:04:37.150
Amen.

00:04:39.033 --> 00:04:46.483
When I was in Bible college, I took a semester and went overseas to do my studies in England.

00:04:47.144 --> 00:04:51.330
And while I was there, I realized who knows when I'm ever going to be back.

00:04:51.510 --> 00:04:54.514
And so I want to get everything out of this like can.

00:04:54.594 --> 00:04:56.737
We were allowed to travel on the weekends.

00:04:56.857 --> 00:05:05.390
And so two, three weekends out of the month, I would go somewhere, explore something, try and explore the city I lived in, which was York, England.

00:05:05.791 --> 00:05:07.233
It was a weird year to be there.

00:05:07.253 --> 00:05:08.154
It was 2001.

00:05:08.595 --> 00:05:10.097
I was there during September 11.

00:05:10.137 --> 00:05:24.178
I was standing in a fish and chip shop watching on television as the planes are crashing into this tower and being in old York while this was all going on in New York and being separated from family knowing if I wanted to, I couldn't fly home.

00:05:24.482 --> 00:05:27.448
It was very disequilibriating to be there.

00:05:27.488 --> 00:05:38.109
But I loved and I look back fondly on many of the trips, going to Edinburgh, Scotland, and visiting and touring, spending a weekend down in London and staying in a hostel.

00:05:38.129 --> 00:05:45.223
But one of the most memorable trips was when a few of us went to a city that everyone told us you've got to see it to believe it.

00:05:45.263 --> 00:05:46.866
It's called Lindisfarne.

00:05:47.010 --> 00:05:47.711
Lindisfarne.

00:05:48.132 --> 00:05:53.884
And it's a tidal island, and a tidal island that you can only access certain times of the day.

00:05:54.065 --> 00:06:06.130
So sometimes when you approach this 1,000-acre island, which is at the north of England, just below Scotland, you look at it and you go, there's no way I can get there unless I hire a boat to take me out there because it looks like there's no way.

00:06:06.210 --> 00:06:10.295
But then the tide goes out, and a road is revealed.

00:06:10.475 --> 00:06:15.281
And there is, in fact, a road that you can drive to this island, but you have to time it just right.

00:06:15.301 --> 00:06:19.887
You can only during a few hours in the morning and a few hours in the evening drive there.

00:06:19.927 --> 00:06:28.818
And once you're there, you're there because this tidal island is completely cut off from vehicles getting in when the tide comes in.

00:06:28.898 --> 00:06:36.745
And so if you live there, or if you want to visit there, you have to consult the Lindisfarne website, which has a title chart that tells you what times of day you can commute by car.

00:06:36.825 --> 00:06:42.370
And it looks like this, where you say, OK, safe to cross, unsafe to cross, safe to cross, unsafe to cross.

00:06:42.630 --> 00:06:48.055
And there are literally, we went in in the morning, and then we started touring, saw this castle, found something to eat.

00:06:48.095 --> 00:06:51.297
And then the tide comes in, and the water comes up.

00:06:51.378 --> 00:06:54.380
The moon starts pulling on the ocean, because that's how that works, by the way.

00:06:54.780 --> 00:06:58.884
And all of a sudden, we're like, oh yeah, you can't go anywhere, because we had come in by car, we had no access

00:06:58.864 --> 00:06:59.645
access to a boat.

00:07:00.045 --> 00:07:02.248
And so now here we are, six or seven college students.

00:07:02.308 --> 00:07:03.529
And we were like, we're stuck.

00:07:03.809 --> 00:07:05.971
We've seen the things that there are to do on Linda's farm.

00:07:06.572 --> 00:07:10.116
And well, one thing led to another.

00:07:10.456 --> 00:07:15.682
And the closest I ever came to getting arrested while living in England actually took place on Linda's farm.

00:07:16.282 --> 00:07:18.024
Save that story for a different day.

00:07:18.064 --> 00:07:27.314
But it felt so weird to be at a place where we literally couldn't leave this island because this water had risen, which is at the center

00:07:27.426 --> 00:07:45.643
of Ezekiel's vision that we've just read here, where an angel has come to him to show him something of what God's going to do in a hopeless situation and the encouragement that he gave to Ezekiel and by extension to the whole nation of Israel and ultimately to us.

00:07:45.743 --> 00:07:57.394
And all of God's people have lived under the hope and the promise, and it all centers around a river, a river that comes from the altar, a river that comes from the altar and leaves through a temple.

00:07:57.570 --> 00:08:04.298
A river that comes from the altar and leaves the temple and comes through a gate and eventually flows to all of us.

00:08:04.979 --> 00:08:11.827
And this, obviously, is something that is all a prophetic description of what God was going to do through Jesus.

00:08:12.508 --> 00:08:14.731
We know that because it involves an altar.

00:08:14.771 --> 00:08:16.773
We know that because it involves a temple.

00:08:16.793 --> 00:08:18.996
We know that because it involves a gate.

00:08:19.797 --> 00:08:24.242
On the altar in the temple that you access by going through the gate,

00:08:24.322 --> 00:08:28.907
was this picture of sacrifice and what it would take to have a right relationship with God.

00:08:29.568 --> 00:08:31.109
And Ezekiel was living at a time.

00:08:31.129 --> 00:08:37.697
He wrote this somewhere around 597 BC at a time when all hope seemed like it was lost.

00:08:38.257 --> 00:08:49.970
He wrote this at a time when he was living as a captive alongside 10,000 or so others at a little colony alongside a river, a river called the Kibar River in Babylon.

00:08:50.082 --> 00:08:55.548
And we know that he was there because even in the first chapter of his book, he said it came to pass and he dates it.

00:08:56.029 --> 00:09:08.443
And then he says, as I was among the captives, this is Ezekiel 1 verse 1, I was among the captives by the river Kebar that the heavens opened, and there I saw visions of God.

00:09:09.204 --> 00:09:14.130
And the angel came to show him that God was one day going to

00:09:14.434 --> 00:09:16.681
Bring about a river that would water the whole world.

00:09:16.722 --> 00:09:17.905
How is it going to happen?

00:09:17.925 --> 00:09:22.962
It was going to happen through a temple and water coming out from under the altar and coming out through a door.

00:09:23.522 --> 00:09:28.368
Now, at this time, the temple had been seized.

00:09:28.448 --> 00:09:30.670
At this time, the temple had been torn down.

00:09:30.730 --> 00:09:41.222
At the time that these were living in exile, this seemed like completely impossible because of Nebuchadnezzar's armies that had raised the city of Jerusalem to the ground.

00:09:41.422 --> 00:09:51.634
And so as he stood here by a river and saw from the angel of God a promise of a coming river, it seemed completely and totally impossible.

00:09:52.034 --> 00:09:53.116
But it was fulfilled.

00:09:53.176 --> 00:10:03.450
It was fulfilled not only literally when the Jewish people got to return to the Promised Land under men like Zerubbabel and Ezra and Nehemiah.

00:10:03.550 --> 00:10:09.559
And there they actually physically did rebuild the temple and physically did rebuild the walls around the city.

00:10:10.260 --> 00:10:20.274
But much more important, it was fulfilled symbolically in that it was always a picture of what Jesus was going to do because Jesus was

00:10:20.386 --> 00:10:26.034
was always talking about how the temple was actually a picture of his temple, his body.

00:10:26.454 --> 00:10:40.593
In fact, one of the reasons he was put to death that they finally utilized in his trial was his statement from John chapter 2, verse 19, destroy this temple, and I will raise it again in three days.

00:10:41.214 --> 00:10:42.376
And that was what they used.

00:10:42.396 --> 00:10:44.158
They said, oh, he said he's going to tear it on the temple.

00:10:44.178 --> 00:10:46.181
They were trying to bill him as some kind of a terrorist.

00:10:46.461 --> 00:10:49.906
But he wasn't pointing to that temple when he said those words.

00:10:50.018 --> 00:11:00.761
He was pointing to this temple, the temple of his body, that he was the lamb upon the altar that you read about in the Old Testament, that he was that sacrificial lamb.

00:11:00.781 --> 00:11:06.434
Behold, the lamb of God, John the Baptist said, who has come to take away the sins of the world.

00:11:06.814 --> 00:11:08.498
So the literal fulfillment

00:11:08.578 --> 00:11:12.523
of Ezekiel's vision here that the temple is going to be rebuilt.

00:11:12.563 --> 00:11:14.505
You're going to live in the land once again.

00:11:14.545 --> 00:11:18.931
The promises God gave to Abraham, these have not been forgotten by God.

00:11:19.251 --> 00:11:20.693
He is going to keep them.

00:11:20.713 --> 00:11:24.537
But they all pointed forward to a day when Jesus Christ would come.

00:11:24.898 --> 00:11:25.839
Who is the temple?

00:11:26.079 --> 00:11:28.202
Who is the lamb upon the altar?

00:11:28.562 --> 00:11:32.847
And who is the gate that you can use to access this new life?

00:11:33.248 --> 00:11:36.312
He said in John chapter 10, verse 9, I am the gate.

00:11:36.692 --> 00:11:38.354
And whoever enters through me,

00:11:38.786 --> 00:11:39.588
will be saved.

00:11:39.969 --> 00:11:44.058
He will come in and go out and find pasture.

00:11:44.880 --> 00:11:51.314
So this prophecy that this angel gave to Ezekiel, the priest, who had a unique connection to the temple.

00:11:51.586 --> 00:11:58.812
and who had been sadder than anybody standing by the river Kebar and remembering glory days when there was a temple.

00:11:58.832 --> 00:12:05.098
Glory days when the people of Israel lived in and accessed the city of Jerusalem, the city of peace.

00:12:05.118 --> 00:12:10.643
He more than most would have had this nostalgic sense of hopelessness over what was gone.

00:12:10.983 --> 00:12:13.465
And the angel comes from God with an assignment.

00:12:13.665 --> 00:12:15.006
I know you feel abandoned.

00:12:15.086 --> 00:12:16.327
I know you feel forgotten.

00:12:16.368 --> 00:12:18.569
I know you feel like your greatest days are behind you.

00:12:18.790 --> 00:12:19.891
But I got news for you.

00:12:20.171 --> 00:12:21.572
There is a gate.

00:12:21.552 --> 00:12:26.959
is a temple and there is a river, a river who makes glad the cities of God.

00:12:27.100 --> 00:12:28.306
And the point of this

00:12:28.354 --> 00:12:35.821
Literal fulfillment of this temple being rebuilt was to point forward to the symbolic fulfillment of what God was saying through it.

00:12:36.201 --> 00:12:51.676
And that is that through Jesus being on the altar of the cross, through Jesus going into the holy of holies with his own sacrifice for us, that issuing forth from that temple, issuing forth from that building, flowing out, we could access life through him.

00:12:52.297 --> 00:12:58.002
And so we had this picture of a river coming out to make glad the cities of God, which

00:12:58.242 --> 00:13:01.087
Psalm 46.4 says is a reality.

00:13:01.648 --> 00:13:05.856
So this vision is both literal and it's symbolic.

00:13:06.337 --> 00:13:10.945
And it is also, from our perspective, both past and it is future.

00:13:11.686 --> 00:13:12.968
It's both past and future.

00:13:13.309 --> 00:13:13.870
What do I mean?

00:13:13.930 --> 00:13:20.562
Well, I mean, we can, from where we sit here in the year 2021, look back and go, yeah, the Jews did go back.

00:13:20.674 --> 00:13:21.635
into the promised land.

00:13:21.656 --> 00:13:23.158
They did live there once again.

00:13:23.198 --> 00:13:25.121
The temple did get rebuilt.

